Cryptographic standards referenced and corroborated:

- FIPS 204 (ML-DSA), FIPS 203 (ML-KEM) — NIST post-quantum standards.
- NIST ACVP test vectors (public domain, U.S. Government) — used to corroborate the
  ML-DSA-65 signing spine. Corroboration against published vectors is NOT an
  independent cryptographic audit.
- RFC 6962 / RFC 9162 (Certificate Transparency) — the append-only Merkle history
  pattern; corroborated against the CT reference vectors.

